    "description": "<p>You can see heat gradients, allowing you a somewhat blurry vision that functions even in perfect darkness or clouds of dust. This thermal vision is precise enough to distinguish individuals, but cannot make out fine details. As a Main Action, you can emit ocular heat rays that do 2d6 damage plus your character level to a target within 30 meters, with an Evasion save to negate it. Each use of this ability after the first in a scene adds one System Strain.</p>",
